1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:27,431
Prayer to Saint Theophan the Recluse Pray slowly. Read with attention.

2
00:00:27,431 --> 00:00:35,049
O Holy Bishop Theophan, you taught us that the essence of prayer is to stand before God with the mind in the heart, constantly remembering His presence. Pray for us, dear

3
00:00:35,049 --> 00:00:42,668
father, that we may be delivered from wandering and distracted thoughts. Teach us to practice the memory of God throughout our busy days, holding fast to His name in

4
00:00:42,668 --> 00:00:50,287
every circumstance.

5
00:00:50,287 --> 00:00:58,564
O wise scribe of the Spirit, you spent your days in study and translation, sharing the deep treasures of Orthodox spirituality with the world through your letters

6
00:00:58,564 --> 00:01:06,840
and books. Grant us the desire for spiritual learning and the wisdom to understand the teachings of the fathers. Guide our minds to seek truth, and preserve us from

7
00:01:06,840 --> 00:01:15,117
intellectual pride and spiritual self-deception.

8
00:01:15,117 --> 00:01:23,351
O quiet recluse, you found complete peace of soul behind closed doors, turning your small cell into a sanctuary of prayer and labor. When we feel lonely, isolated, or

9
00:01:23,351 --> 00:01:31,585
forgotten by the world, help us to recognize these moments as invitations to closer union with God. Calm our anxious hearts, and fill our solitude with the

10
00:01:31,585 --> 00:01:39,819
comforting presence of Christ.

11
00:01:39,819 --> 00:01:53,771
Saint Theophan the Recluse, pray to God for us. Amen.

